<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="239" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,541,1826]" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1549,1574]" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after the great biochemist and firefly collector Vadim Viviani, who has strongly promoted the study of the 
<taxonomicName box="[544,679,1585,1610]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lampyridae</taxonomicName>
and other bioluminescent beetles in 
<collectingCountry box="[1090,1162,1585,1610]" name="Brazil" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="239" type="discussion">
